Scope note

This MIT license covers the ORIGINAL work in this repository: the
reverse-engineering notes, analysis tooling, patches, and the community
firmware reconstruction under `firmware/`, `re/notes/`, `re/scripts/`, and
`re/patches/`.

It does NOT cover, and no license is granted over:
  - `Compiled FW/B288-REV1.0.hex` — the vendor's already-publicly-distributed
    firmware binary, included only as a reference for interoperability/repair
    reverse engineering. All rights to it remain with its author.
  - `re/binja/*` — Binary Ninja disassembly/decompilation artifacts contributed
    by @Mixcatonic (ModWiggler); included with thanks, credited in the README.

"Buchla" and "288" are used only to identify the hardware this project targets;
no affiliation or endorsement is claimed.
